com.splunk.journal

Class EventData

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.splunk.journal.EventData

  • public class EventData
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents data read from a journal file about one particular event. Instances may be re-used for efficiency, so should not be cached.

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getFields()
        Gets a mapping from name to value for "extra" fields stored with this event, ie. other than event time, host, source, or sourcetype. Each values will be either a String or a Number object (Long, BigNumber>, Float, or Double).
